   13. GUNS, GERMS AND STEEL, by Jared Diamond. (Norton,
</P>
<P>
   $14.95.) A physiologist attributes Western dominance
</P>
<P>
   to geography. (b)
</P>
<P>
   14. TRAVELING MERCIES, by Anne Lamott. (Anchor, $13.)
</P>
<P>
   A chronicle of the author's journey toward faith and
</P>
<P>
   spirituality.
</P>
<P>
   15. EVERY MAN A TIGER, by Tom Clancy with Chuck Horner.
</P>
<P>
   (Berkley, $16.95.) The novelist and a retired Air Force
</P>
<P>
   general examine the Gulf war.
