</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    What do you want to be when you grow up?
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   stats.bls.gov/k12/html/eduover.htm _ You may be too young to
find a summer job, but it isn't too early to start thinking about
what you'd like to do when you grow up. This is a good site to
learn about some of those careers you've dreamed of: architect,
politician, dancer, computer repairman and 30 others. The
professions are arranged by academic area, so you can find what job
might suit you by clicking on your favorite subject in school. Read
about what the career is like, how to prepare for it, the salary
range and more. The site also includes links and snail mail
addresses to learn more.
</P>
<P>
   aggie-horticulture.tamu.edu/kindergarden/kinder.htm _ Learn
about how you can start your own vegetable garden in a park, at
school, or in the backyard. This site, operated by Texas A&AMP;M
University, offers tips for kids and parents on gardening as a
family. It includes a list of fun project ideas, such as making a
scarecrow, drying flowers or keeping a garden journal.
</P>
