<P>
   SING AROUND THE SOLAR-POWERED CAMPSITE
</P>
<P>
   SOLAR-GADGETS-POPMECH _ Clear sunlight contains 1,000 watts of
power per square meter at sea level. That's enough to power
everything on Earth 1,500 times over if we could just figure out a
way to harness all the free, nonstop solar energy that bathes the
globe every day. Of course, in a very real sense everything on
Earth is already solar-powered _ we just release that power in
different ways. Burning long-buried hydrocarbons to get at stored
solar energy, as we've been doing, isn't particularly efficient.
But other ways to use solar energy are available. There's a whole
campsite worth of clever outdoor gear that runs directly on
sunlight. By Rich Taylor.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of solar-powered outdoor equipment are
available on Newscom or by calling William Gonzalez at
212-499-3355.)
</P>
