<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington)_ Bill Bradley's belated endorsement of
Vice President Al Gore last week enables Gore to present a
united-party front at the Democratic convention. But the move did
less for Gore than for Bradley, who looked as though he were going
for the sour grapes cup long thought to have been retired by Eugene
McCarthy 30 years ago. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
