<TEXT>
<P>
   EDITORS: The James Lileks commentary column slugged
``LILEKS-GREEN,'' transmitted July 11, has been killed. For those
papers who published the column, we are providing the following
corrective:
</P>
<P>
   The James Lileks commentary column slugged ``LILEKS-GREEN,''
transmitted July 11, attributed certain political positions to the
Green Party and, by extension, to Ralph Nader. The column was based
on a Web site other than that of the Association of State Green
Parties, which nominated Nader as its presidential candidate in
June. The positions described in the column were drawn from
www.greenparty.org, the Web site of the Green Party USA. While that
organization has endorsed Nader and solicits money for his
candidacy, its views diverge from those of the Association of State
Green Parties.
</P>
</TEXT>
