</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With INTERNET-SOFTWARE. Moving in (w) Washington and (f)
financial categories for release Sunday, July 23.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Pity the late-arriving entrepreneur who decides to take his
business on line.
</P>
<P>
   Suppose a fisherman creates a fly that catches trout like magic.
He decides to create a Web site to market it.
</P>
<P>
   But he'll find the waters are nearly fished out. A visit to the
Web site of Network Solutions, a company that registers domain
names for a fee, responds with ``Sorry, (that site) is not
available'' when one tries to register:
</P>
<P>
   _ fishing.com
</P>
<P>
   _ flyfishing.com
</P>
<P>
   _ fly-fishing.com
</P>
<P>
   _ fly.com
</P>
<P>
   _ flies.com
</P>
<P>
   _ lures.com
</P>
<P>
   _ mylure.com
</P>
<P>
   _ fishcatcher.com
</P>
<P>
   _ catchatrout.com
</P>
<P>
   _ gone-fishing.com
</P>
