interest rates unchanged, citing in part the bankruptcy of the
retailer Sogo. Until Wednesday's bankruptcy filing, the central
bank had been widely expected to raise rates by a quarter point, to
0.27 percent, which would have been the first rate increase since
1990. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   (With graphic.)
